        description: 'Create two NodePools: a Spot pool for fault-tolerant workloads and an On-Demand pool for critical or stateful workloads. The Spot pool uses a broad instance family list (m5, m5a, m5d, c5, c5a, r5 and their xlarge+ variants) — Karpenter picks the cheapest available type at launch, and diversification across families and sizes reduces interruption probability. Set the On-Demand pool as a fallback using the karpenter.sh/capacity-type: on-demand nodeSelector. Pods declare their preference via nodeSelector or a weighted PodTopologySpread, not hard node affinity — they should still schedule if the preferred pool is unavailable.',
